Flames shot out of Thassalin's mouth as the huge Thracian set a specific forest patch on fire and then circled over it to recognize movements. Notably, the eerie screaming behind him subsided as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
“What's that, Tenuk, you've turned into a Thracian before!”
“When I fly myself, it's completely different from being suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!”
“It wasn't that bad, was it, Kayel?”
Kayel was obviously not in agreement with Nyssis. He looked less black than usual and his claws had dug so deep into Thassalin's back that the Thracian was bleeding. Thassalin seemed not to care, but it had become clear to him that he had scared his new friends, and he landed on a clearing.
“I'M SORRY, BUT I SMELLED SOMETHING. SO I HAD TO TAKE CARE OF IT!”
“But did you have to drag us along too?” growled Tenuk as he climbed off Thassalin's back and slid down his tail. “And we left Retvik behind! Our big, strong fighter is all alone! How is he going to catch up with us?”
“He'll think of something…”, growled Nyssi. “Retvik isn't the fastest, but he's not stupid.”
“Okay, but can Retvik fly?”
Nyssi winked and turned back to Tenuk. “Of course, he can fly.”
"Have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive a nice little car like Kayel's. He only just started using the car for work because you always drive us. He has only his bicycle."
Loud laughter interrupted them. Thassalin seemed to find something wildly funny suddenly, but no one knew what he was laughing about. It took a bit too long for Thassalin to calm down.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I PRESENTED YOUR HUGE FRIEND ON A LITTLE BICYCLE FOR TEMTHAN KIDS. THAT WAS KILLING ME! I WISH I HAD SOME KIND OF TELEPATHY. A WONDERFUL IMAGINATION! ONE I CANNOT SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, thinking he knew what was going on in Thassalin's head. "Yes, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?"
Thassalin grunted, took off, and disappeared. When he returned a short time later, he threw something lifeless at Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, golden-white dragon creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR THEIR SCREAMS. I SMELL THEIR BLOOD. SOMETHING IS DRIVING ME TO PROTECT AND HUNT. LIKE YISINI INSTRUCTED. THEY ARE VERY CLOSE."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and looked intently at a gap in the clearing. Something large and black stared at them and snarled. What it was, it spread out two enormous wing pairs and shot towards Thassalin without caring about the three smaller creatures between them. Kayel and Tenuk could just barely take cover, but Nyssi was swept along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin responded to this attack by snatching Nyssi and slinging him onto his back with his incredibly long and skilled tail, before he himself took to the air. The black, double-winged creature pursued them at high speed.
Kayel snorted in annoyance as he took his rifle from his back and opened a pouch that contained a ammunition belt. He hung the belt over his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were out of sight.
"Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?" Kayel asked.
"You want to pursue them?"
“Yes, of course!”
“But… One of them is a huge monster!”
“Yes and? I'm standing here with a high-end rifle in my hand and could shoot at it immediately. But, well, how can I say this – I would have to be able to see it in order to hit it.”
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to give himself more space. With a soft, painful growl, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turned to scales, and his arms turned to wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, light blue Thracian, but his eyes remained red.
“Get on.”
Tenuk now had a proper scaly shield on his back, resembling a typical Thracian. Conveniently, a pair of spines had also grown on his back, which Kayel could hold onto. It took a bit longer for Tenuk to get airborne, but once he was in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to take up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel soon realized they weren't alone. A second dark creature shot up beneath them, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid a collision.
"Is that the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel furrowed his brow. He tried to shoot at the second beast, missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk didn't respond. He was too busy focusing on flying towards Nyssi and Thassalin, even though the other beast was pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep an eye on the monster. The fact that it was pursuing them was a advantage for Kayel, as he could easily aim and fire. Two shots went through the upper wings of the beast. It let out a pained roar and sank back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it wouldn't be able to keep up.
A good distance ahead, Nyssi clung desperately to something, while Thassalin swung his arms and spat fire at the blackened monster. The creature was definitely injured. It seemed angry but not ready to give up. The fireballs seemed to have no effect. As Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw his own weapon, an old shotgun. It wasn't exactly the first choice, but perhaps the buckshot would scare the black beast away.
